<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-23T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-23T20:00:00-05:00" n="175" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d175">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.00/1322a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador to the Greek Government in Exile</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacVeagh</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">at Cairo</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-23T21:00:00-04:00">December
                                    23, 1943—9 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Greek [Series] 66. The British and Greek Ambassadors have both requested
                            the public support of this Government to the Greek Premier’s <pb facs="0176" n="164" xml:id="pg_164"/> radio appeal of December 21
                            for Greek unity. I understand that a similar request has been made of
                            the Soviet Government.</p>
                        <p>You are authorized to deliver to the Prime Minister for use as he desires
                            the message contained in the Department’s next following telegram.<note n="69" xml:id="d175fn69">
                                <hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi>
                            </note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>